title: Swanson Shootout-Running
description: Off-road running race through Swanson Park. Post race food and awards to the top 3 in each category.
registration:
Entry Fee is $15 per runner by preregistering online by 7pm, Friday, March 31. 
Cost increases to $25 per runner on the day of the race. 
Registration closes 30 minutes prior to the actual race. 
Cash or checks only on site.
notes: Awards of medals will be awarded to the top 3 runners in each category.
directions:
Swanson Park
3110 Cornhusker Rd
Bellevue, NE  
Look for Fire Station Training Center sign on north side of Cornhusker.

title: Swanson Shootout 2017
description: XC, Marathon and Trail Running Races
course:
Race loop is approximately 4.5 miles for all levels. 

Swanson Park is a fast, flowing course of mostly single track with some really nice technical sections including log crossings, g-outs and bowls. It loops tightly within a relatively small area, so you’re never far from the start.
registration:
PRE-REGISTRATION : Pre-registration cut off is Friday, March 31, 7 p.m.

Racers under the age of 18 need a parent or guardian to register them and sign the waiver at the event.

Register at USA Cycling and log into your account using your license number. This does not mean you have to buy a license. This is just to sign up for the race. If you do not have a license then just create an account. You will then use this account for the rest of the season. If you do have a license, then you don’t need to start a new account. Log in with your license number.

DAY-OF REGISTRATION : Day-of registration can only be done at the race venue. The cost is $10 on top of your entry fee. 

Cut off time for same day registration is 30 minutes before your event.
notes:
RACE SCHEDULE
8:00am, Trail Run Race
9:30am, Trail Run Podium Presentation for top 3 racers in each cat. 
9:00am Junior MTB Races
10:00am Marathon MEN & WOMEN, CAT 3 WOMEN & MEN  
11:30am Awards Ceremony Cat 3 & Juniors Top 3 will receive medals 
12:00pm Cat 1 Men and Women Mountain Bike Races
12:02 pm Cat 2 Mountain Bike Races
2:30pm Kiddie Bike Races for U 10
2:45 pm Awards Ceremony Cat 1/2/Marathon 

PAYOUT
Gift Cards will be given to top 3 finishers in Cat 2; Cash will be awarded to the top 5 in Marathon Men 40+ & U39 and top 3 in Marathon Women. Equal payouts among men and women. Turnout determines how deep payouts are for Cat 1 Men & Women combined, with the max being $100 for the winner. Equal payouts for both men and women. 

RACE DISTANCES
Trail Run, 1 lap; Marathon – 4 hours;  Cat 3 – 1 Lap; Cat 2 – 3 Laps; Cat 1 – 5 Laps; Kids – Course TBD
directions: From Omaha; take Hwy 75 south from I-80 to the Cornhusker Rd. exit. Go west on Cornhusker to approximately 32nd St. Look for a brick sign with scrolling red letters for the Fire Department Training Center. Turn north and the park entrance is about 50 yards down the road on the left. You can park in the lot and on the entrance road up to the gate.  If gate is open, we can park on the road.

title: 2017 R&R Outside Ride Right MTB School #1
description: Beginner and intermediate mountain bike skills clinic for adult men and women. This clinic is co-ed, ages 18+.
course: Day 1 will be at Tranquility Park. We'll spend most of the days doing "grass room" drills before heading out onto actual trails. Day 2 will be at Swanson Park. We'll start the day doing new drills, utilizing the grassy open hillsides before working our way onto the trails.
registration: Cost is $195 per person. The fee includes certified instruction for two days, lunch, snacks, swag and high fives!
notes: All participants are required to have a valid USAC annual or one day license. This is required for insurance purposes.
directions:
Tranquility Park is located just west of 120th & Fort. We will stage on the south side of Fort next to the soccer fields. 

Swanson Park is located at 31st & Cornhusker Rd in Bellevue. Look for the Bellevue Fire Dept. Training Center sign on north side of street.

Star City CX - Van Dorn Park #1
NICS #1 - Tranquility Park
description: NICS #1 will be a multi-lap mountain bike race at Tranquility Park in Omaha.
course:
The single-track course will use 1.8 miles of the south side Creek Trail and the north-facing side of the South Hill trail.
Lap counts and start times are listed below
registration: If you don't sign up through your club team, the cost to sign up online is $10 per racer without an annual license. If you sign up at the event, it's $20 per racer. Annual licenses can be purchased for $35 at any race or usacycling.com where you will need to set up an account for your under-age racer. Parents or guardians will have to bring a signed waiver to each race or sign one at the event. All racers need to be registered online by 7pm, Sept. 8.
notes: All racers must wear a helmet and school-affiliated t-shirt to be eligible to race. Racers should arrive no later than 30 minutes prior to their start time. directions: Tranquility Mountain Bike Park is at 122nd & Fort Street. The entrance to the park is located off of Fort. There is no access from Maple Street. Please park in the gravel lot next to soccer fields. Look for signs directing racers and fans to the staging area.

title: R&R Outside- Ride Right MTB School #3
description:
Single-day MTB School
Saturday, September 23rd
8:30 am - 5 pm

8:30 - 9:00 am Arrive at venue, make introductions, get bike ready
9:00 - 11:30 am Grass room and trail practice
11:30 - 12:15 Lunch break on site
12:30 - 2:45 Early afternoon session
2:45 - Rest Break
3:00 - 4:40 pm Later afternoon session
4:40 - 5:00 Final words, fill out survey

This single-day beginner to intermediate mountain bike skills clinic is  for adult men and women. If you are just getting into mountain biking or have been at if a few years and want to progress, this clinic is for you! 

The goal of the course is to get folks comfortable with their bikes, understanding the basics of riding positions and bike handling so that you can return to your favorite trails with the knowledge you need to practice and continue to improve and develop confidence.
course:
Tranquility MTB Park is a 9 mile trail system in northwest Omaha. We'll start the clinic doing "grass room" drills before heading out to practice on the trails. 

The trails have a variety of terrain and features that we will utilize to instruct and practice. We will not take riders in areas that are above their skill level and at no time will you be pressured into riding. This is a classroom environment. We're all here to learn!
registration: Registration fee for a single-day skills clinic is $105. This includes personal instruction, catered lunch & snacks.
notes:
Participants are required to wear a helmet and we prefer that you use flat pedals. We have pedals to loan out if you don't have any. 

We recommend wearing comfortable clothes and bring layers as the weather warms throughout the day. 

Bring water and sunscreen.
directions: Tranquility Park is located just west of 120th on Fort Street. We will stage on the south side of Fort St. in the gravel lot next to the soccer fields. Look for a black pop up tent.

title: Star City CX - Van Dorn Park #2
NICS #3 - Swanson Park Mountain Bike Race
description:
This is a cross country mountain bike race at Swanson Park in Bellevue. 

Each age group and category will race to see who can do the required laps the fastest.

All athletes are required to wear a helmet and a shirt with the school's name on it.

Please arrive and register 30 minutes prior to the start time.

Awards will be presented immediately after.
course: Swanson Park is a purpose built mountain bike park. They are twisty and wind through the trees. Expect tree roots and a few log-overs.
registration: Please be registered either through your team-club or if you are an independent with no team-club, please register online by 7pm, Sept. 7.
notes: Varsity will go first followed by JV.

title: NICS #5
description:
Race #5 is the final event and mountain bike race of the 2017 series. Not only will racers be awarded for this race but also for the season. After all the races are finished, we invite all racers and their families to attend the Season Awards Banquet in the dining hall at Camp Calvin Crest.

The day's schedule:
2:30 JV
2:40 Non-highschool 
3:30 Varsity
5:00 Season Awards Presentation & Potluck
course:
The course is almost entirely single track in the hilly woods surrounding the camp. 

Each lap is around 3 miles.
JV - 2 laps 
Non-highschool - 1 lap
Varsity - 3 laps
registration:
All team-club racers who have paid for the season are considered registered. 

Any racers not affiliated with a school the cost is $20 to race and should register online at usacycling.com.
notes:
All racers are required to wear a helmet and a shirt representing their school.

All racers are required to present a signed waiver in order to get their number plate.
directions:
The camp is located just south of Fremont proper on the banks of the Platte River. 

The address is 2870 Co Rd 13, Fremont, NE 68025. Please use Google Maps for driving directions. https://www.google.com/maps/dir/''/camp+calvin+crest/@41.4189767,-96.5793073,13z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m9!4m8!1m0!1m5!1m1!1s0x87915d7e9daf2b7f:0xe909b82d182f78dc!2m2!1d-96.544288!2d41.418982!3e0
